O'Brien","Eddisbury","Mr Stephen O'Brien","196161"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48076","HM Treasury","false","2014-04-28","<p>Officials discuss a variety of VAT issues with the European Commission and the officials of other Member States.</p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2014-04-28T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48076/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48076/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48076/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2014-04-09","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what recent discussions officials in his Department have had with their EU counterparts on (a) VAT rates on e-books, digital magazines and newspapers and (b) application of reduced rates; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr Aidan Burley","Cannock Chase","Mr Aidan Burley","196173"
