"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/47485","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2014-04-28","<p>An apprenticeship is a job with an accompanying skills development programme designed by employers in the sector to meet the key requirements of the job role. In many cases this will include an aspect of customer service as many jobs recognise the importance of such skills and these will be reflected in the apprenticeship framework.</p><p> </p><p>More than 400 employers are involved in the development of new apprenticeship standards as part of our Trailblazers programme. Where they see customer service skills as crucial to an occupation, they will include these within the new employer-led standards.</p><p> </p><p>For individuals in jobs that are specific customer service roles there is a dedicated Customer Service Apprenticeship available.</p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock",,"2014-04-28T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/47485/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/47485/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/47485/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2014-04-08","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what steps his Department has taken to introduce customer service training in the apprenticeship programme.","false","Biography information for Ann McKechin","Glasgow North","Ann McKechin","195934"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/47486","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2014-04-28","<p>No firms have received bonuses in relation to the sale of Royal Mail shares.</p>","Sevenoaks","Michael Fallon","195939","2014-04-28T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/47486/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/47486/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/47486/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2014-04-08","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, for which firms his Department has agreed bonus payments as part of the privatisation of Royal Mail; and on what criteria such payments were made.","false","Biography information for Ann McKechin","Glasgow North","Ann McKechin","195936"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/47487","Department for Education","false","2014-04-28","<p>We are making available approximately £75 million revenue funding over the course of the 2014-15 and 2015-16 financial years to enable sixth-form and further education colleges to provide free meals to disadvantaged 16- to 18-year-old students.</p><p>We will publish advice on the funding and implementation of this policy shortly.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock",,"2014-04-28T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/47487/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/47487/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/47487/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2014-04-08","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, whether he plans to provide capital funding for sixth form colleges to enable them to provide free school meals to disadvantaged pupils.","false","Biography information for Dr Julian Huppert","Cambridge","Dr Julian Huppert","195955"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/47488","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2014-04-28","<p>There are currently six appointed Business Ambassadors covering the Professional and Business Services Sector: Caroline Plumb – CEO FreshMinds, Alan Parker – Chairman Brunswick Group, Ruby McGregor-Smith CBE – CEO MITIE, Rona Fairhead CBE, Will Lawes – Senior Partner Freshfields Bruchaus Deringer and Steve Varley – UK Chairman and Managing Partner (UK and Ireland) EY.</p><p> </p><p>Business Ambassadors are appointed by the Prime Minister to act as advocates of the UK, promoting the UK's excellence, economy, business environment and its reputation as the international trade and inward investment partner of choice.</p><p> </p><p>Business Ambassadors agree to undertake a programme of activities agreed with UK Trade &amp; Investment (UKTI) including, among others, holding events to promote UK businesses around the world, meeting overseas Ministers and inward missions; participating in trade missions; and providing insights into how UKTI can best deliver for business.</p>","Sevenoaks","Michael Fallon",,"2014-04-28T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/47488/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/47488/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/47488/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2014-04-08","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, how many professional and business services special envoys have been appointed by his Department; and what the remit of those envoys is.","false","Biography information for Ann McKechin","Glasgow North","Ann McKechin","195937"
